100 REM PROGRAM TO COMPUTE AND SHOW SALARY COMPOSITION
110 REM DP1 IS THE DEDUCTION FOR SOCIAL SECURITY AND TAXES (%)
120 REM H IS THE N. OF HOURS WORKED IN A MONTH
130 REM I IS THE HOURLY INCOME RATE ($ PER HOURS)
140 REM INPUT DATA ARE INSERTED INTERACTIVELY BY THE USER
150 GOSUB 1000
255 REM GET WORKER INPUT DATA 
260 PRINT "WORKER (NAME SURNAME)";: INPUT W$
265 PRINT "DEDUCTION RATE (% [0-100])";: INPUT DP1
270 PRINT "N. OF HOURS WORKED IN A MONTH";: INPUT H
280 PRINT "HOURLY INCOME RATE ($ PER HOUR)";: INPUT I
285 LET DP = DP1/100
290 LET G = H*I : REM COMPUTE GROSS WAGE
300 LET N = G - (G*DP) : REM COMPUTE NET WAGE
310 GOSUB 2000
400 PRINT "DO YOU WANT TO INSERT OTHER WORKERS DATA";: INPUT A$
410 IF LEFT$(A$, 1) = "Y" OR LEFT$(A$, 1) = "y" THEN 255
420 PRINT "GOODBYE."
600 END
